exercise.p:
Consider the following presentation for solving the equation from the previous problem.
\begin{aligned} 7x \amp = x + 24 \\ 7x - x \amp = x + 24 - x \amp \eqnspacer \amp \text{Subtract $x$ from both sides} \\ 7x - x \amp = x - x + 24 \amp \amp \text{Rearrange the terms} \\ 7x - x \amp = (x - x) + 24 \amp \amp \text{Group the terms} \\ (7 - 1)x \amp = (1 - 1)x + 24 \amp \amp \text{Factor out the $x$} \\ 6x \amp = 0x + 24 \amp \amp \text{Arithmetic} \\ 6x \amp = 24 \amp \amp \text{Simplify} \\ \frac{6x}{6} \amp = \frac{24}{6} \amp \amp \text{Divide both sides by $6$} \\ x \amp = 4 \amp \amp \text{Arithmetic} \end{aligned}
The work above is all technically correct. Why do you think this would be considered a problematic presentation?
